    {
      "id": "ans",
      "title": "AND",
      "description": "These pieces represent the point of reflection where slowness becomes meditation. In our current context, it is said that manual processes and traditional trades are destined to disappear in the face of the urgency and immediacy of a society that wants everything \"now.\" As the restless people in my homeland say: \"Yesterday was already too late.\"\n\nTo me, this work defends the idea that art carries within it the artist's thoughts, the empirical wisdom of their ancestors, their tradition, and, fundamentally, their unique vision of the world they know. Visually, the work captures this dialogue between time, memory, and the resistance of the handmade.\n\nMATERIALS: Glass beads, semi-precious stones, thread.",
